# Project Conventions (eskerra-go only)

US English and other cross-repo conventions come from synced `language.mdc` (see AGENTS.md).

Rules:

- UI code must not read files directly.
- UI code must not call Git directly.
- Composables receive state and callbacks only.
- ViewModels depend on repositories or use cases, not Android Context.
- Git operations live only in data/git.
- Markdown parsing and wiki-link resolution live outside UI.
- Inbox editability is a domain rule: inbox notes editable, all other notes read-only.
- Manual vault sync (`ManualSyncNow`) commits all safe local changes with auto-merge on divergence; RSS refresh delegates to the same engine; mark-as-played uses a scoped podcast-only channel (shared git mutex; see sync-hardening spec).
- No WorkManager/AlarmManager scheduled background sync.
- No multi-workspace support.
- Prefer small files. Module size is enforced mechanically at **400** lines (touch it, tidy it) — see AGENTS.md § Module size budget and `specs/team-scalability/README.md`.
- Every feature slice must include at least one unit test for domain/data behavior.

## Quality gate

After changes under `app/src/**` or `*.gradle.kts`, run before marking work complete:

1. `:app:ktlintCheck`
2. `:app:lintDebug`
3. `:app:testDebugUnitTest` when domain, data, or logic changed

Use `./scripts/gradle.sh` for Gradle (sets JDK 17 automatically). Resolve all violations; do not defer to CI.

KtLint uses Android Studio style: keep short parameter lists on one line when they fit. Use `:app:ktlintFormat` only after reviewing the diff.
